Durban - A Glebelands hostel peace committee leader was gunned down on Monday afternoon soon after leaving the uMlazi Magistrate&#x2019;s Court.Police spokeswoman Nqobile Gwala said a 40-year-old man was shot dead in Prince Mcwayizeni Road in uMlazi&#x2019;s V section at about 1.30pm.&#x201C;It is alleged that the deceased was walking along the road when occupants of an unidentified vehicle opened fire towards him and fled.He sustained multiple gunshot wounds and died at the scene,&#x201D; Gwala said. No arrests had been made, she said.According to a statement by Vanessa Burger, a community and human rights activist who has been involved in trying to bring peace to the uMlazi hostel, the killers opened fire on him with rifles and handguns from a white double-cab bakkie.&#x201C;They were experts it seems, injuring no one with whom he had been walking at the time,&#x201D; said Burger. Daily News IOL News on Facebook IOL on Twitter